{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Fj75vNBtS83myCE6DGSAr9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Done.** Here's a summary of what was diagnosed and fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet command hardcoded `.default.svc.cluster.local` in both `--advertise-host` and `--join` flags, but the pods run in the `cockroachdb` namespace. DNS lookups for `crdb-cluster-X.crdb-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local` failed with \"no such host\" because the headless service lives at `crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`.\n\n**Fix:** Patched the StatefulSet to use `$(POD_NAMESPACE)` (already injected as an env var via the downward API) instead of the hardcoded `default`:\n```\n--advertise-host=$(POD_NAME).crdb-cluster.$(POD_NAMESPACE).svc.cluster.local\n--join=crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.$(POD_NAMESPACE).svc.cluster.local:26257,...\n```\n\nThen deleted the pods to force a restart with the corrected template (the rolling update was deadlocked since no pod could pass readiness without init, and init couldn't proceed without correct DNS).\n\n**Result:** All 3 nodes (`crdb-cluster-0/1/2`) are `is_available=true`, `is_live=true`, and the cluster accepts SQL connections."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":526,"cache_read_input_tokens":41540,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":526},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"60c9c589-809b-4cbe-a318-c38c1387f96c","uuid":"d9b0ff4d-2879-469d-a40b-f19fa2677de0","request_id":"req_011Cc4PLgDjWfFywStU24vK4"}
